es\", () => {\nsrc/components/shared/bidding-guides-teaser.test.tsx:48:    const { container } = render(<BiddingGuidesTeaser guides={[]} />);\nsrc/components/shared/site-header.test.tsx:164:  it(\"shows «Настройки» for guides but not travellers in the desktop header dropdown\", async () => {\nsrc/components/shared/__tests__/site-header-admin-gate.test.tsx:50:  it(\"does not expose «Админка» / /admin links to guides\", () => {\n.claude/sot/KODEX.md:189:- **Базовый город** — `base_city` (TEXT). Город, где гид физически базируется. Используется для фильтра входящих запросов: гид видит только запросы, у которых `destination_city ≈ base_city` (case-insensitive). Также для публичного фильтра «Гиды по городу». Добавлена миграцией `20260426000001_plan10_guide_notifications.sql`.\n.claude/sot/KODEX.md:286:Текущие ссылки: **Экскурсии | Гиды | Как это работает**\n.claude/sot/KODEX.md:367:- 2026-05-14 [communication] — При обсуждении тикетов эпика использовать короткие русские ярлыки («Профиль гида», «Страница \"Гиды\"»); полное имя из реестра — только при команде системе или прямой ссылке на тикет; локальные номера «Т1–Т7» не использовать после фиксации дерева.\n.claude/sot/KODEX.md:409:[scope] Make base_city editable in the guide's «О себе» profile block; use it for the «Гиды по городу» public filter.\n.claude/sot/KODEX.md:418:[scope] Trust-strip text under CTA: '✓ Гиды проверены · ✓ Без предоплаты на этапе MVP · ✓ Отмена за 24ч'.\n.claude/sot/KODEX.md:442:[scope] Do not change src, routes, tests, deps, or any application behaviour.\nsrc/lib/profile/guide-verification.ts:3:/** Confirmed guide profile — moderation approved (`guide_profiles.verification_status`). */\nsrc/components/shared/guide-card.tsx:14:    <Link href={`/guides/${guide.slug}`} className=\"block transition-transform hover:-translate-y-1\">\n.claude/sot/INDEX.md:26:- ERR-020 — no direct FK from bookings to guide_profiles; PostgREST join fails\n.claude/sot/INDEX.md:87:- ERR-097 — /admin/guides/[id] returns generic error page for all guides — likely one of the parallel data lookups in getGuideReviewDetail throws on incomplete data (OPEN; blocks visual verify of E-33 T2 Лицензии)\n.claude/sot/INDEX.md:131:- ADR-006 — destination pages render \"Гиды в этом городе\" section (server-fetched, limit 6)\n.claude/sot/INDEX.md:152:- ADR-053 — Push notification \"fill specializations\" deferred; trigger: 30%+ active guides have specs OR 50+ guides on platform within 60d — 2026-05-02\n.claude/sot/INDEX.md:185:- **ERR-092** migration files in repo never applied to live DB (date_flexibility + search_guides_rpc); request creation + guide search were dead; supabase_migrations table unreliable -> ERRORS.md (2026-05-19)\nsrc/components/shared/discovery-search-input.tsx:16: * every discovery page (`/requests`, `/listings`, `/guides`, `/destinations`):\nsrc/lib/copy.ts:80:    step1: 'Гиды видят группу и присылают свои предложения.',\nsrc/lib/supabase/reviews.ts:100:    .from(\"guide_profiles\")\r\nsrc/lib/supabase/bookings.ts:133: * Fetch a single booking by ID with joined guide_profiles, traveler_requests, and guide_offers.\r\nsrc/lib/supabase/bookings.ts:136: * Note: bookings.guide_id has a FK to profiles.id, NOT to guide_profiles.user_id, so\r\nsrc/lib/supabase/bookings.ts:156:      .from(\"guide_profiles\")\r\nsrc/lib/supabase/bookings.ts:158:        \"user_id, bio, rating, completed_tours, is_available, regions, languages, specialties, specialization, attestation_status, verification_status, verification_notes, payout_account_label, years_experience, slug, created_at, updated_at, profile:profiles!guide_profiles_user_id_fkey(full_name, phone, avatar_url)\",\r\nsrc/lib/supabase/bookings.ts:183:  // a strict traveler_id gate. (guide_profiles.display_name was dropped in\r\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:148:- **Symptom:** `/tours` (FEATURE_TR_TOURS=0 → calls `notFound()`), `/guides/[fake-slug]`, `/destinations/[fake-slug]` — all return HTTP 200 with the not-found UI rendered into the body. Conversely `/listings/[fake-id]` returns HTTP 404 correctly.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:267:- **Files Affected:** 7 files in `src/app/(protected)/guide/requests/[requestId]/`, `src/app/(site)/destinations/[slug]/`, `src/app/(site)/guide/[id]/`, `src/app/(site)/guides/[slug]/`, `src/app/(site)/listings/[slug]/`, `src/app/(site)/requests/[requestId]/`, `src/app/(site)/requests/`\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:359:### ERR-020: getBooking PostgREST join fails — no FK from bookings to guide_profiles\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:361:- **Root Cause:** `BOOKING_WITH_DETAILS_SELECT` used `guide_profile:guide_profiles!guide_id(...)`. PostgREST resolved `bookings.guide_id` FK to `profiles.id` — not to `guide_profiles.user_id`. No direct FK exists between `bookings` and `guide_profiles`, so the join was invalid.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:384:- **Symptom:** Dashboard \"от X ₽\" label displayed 80% of the budget the traveler entered; travelers expected to pay X but guides bid at full budget; confusion + decline rate up\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:528:- **Symptom:** Default expiry date on the offer form was one day behind for guides working after 21:00 UTC (00:00 MSK+3). A guide submitting an offer just after midnight Moscow time would see yesterday's date as the default.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:727:- **Symptom:** E-4 \"accounts\" epic shipped node #2 (\"Create canonical themes module — 8 slugs + labels + icons\") that just renamed the existing 8-entry INTEREST_CHIPS into a new src/data/themes.ts and re-exported it. The audit (#1) had documented 7 different listing-vocabulary labels, a drifted religion slug on the homepage form, dual-column specialties/specializations on guide_profiles with a stale trigger, and 5 duplicated label dictionaries. None of these were addressed by the canon. Plan-critique reported PASS confidence=1 concerns=[] anyway. Worker called it: \"канон был написан неправильно, весь эпик надо делать заново\".\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:788:- **Symptom:** Five components (`bid-form-panel.tsx`, `guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx`, `homepage-request-form.tsx`, `active-request-card.tsx`, `traveler-request-detail-screen.tsx`) each owned an inline interest-label dictionary. Three of the four mapped dictionaries included `religion` — a ghost slug absent from `INTEREST_CHIPS` and from the `guide_specializations_valid` DB CHECK constraint. Two dictionaries diverged on `photo` / `Фотопрогулки` (present in inbox, missing from form). Silent symptom: a slug stored via the request form could fall through to the raw `?? s` fallback in the guide inbox or request-detail view, surfacing the bare key string instead of a Russian label.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:812:- **Symptom:** Guides who completed the onboarding wizard had `specializations = '{}'` (empty canonical array) in `guide_profiles`, making them invisible under every `?spec=` filter on `/guides`. The filter queries `.overlaps(\"specializations\", ...)`, but the onboarding wizard had been writing only to the legacy `specialties` (free-text) column. The `auto-sync` trigger `sync_guide_profiles_onboarding_fields` pre-dates the `specializations` column and never touched it.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:814:- **Fix:** Renamed onboarding form field `specialties → specializations`. Replaced `CommaField` free-text input with `InterestChipGroup` (canonical chip UI wired via `Controller`). Tightened Zod schema to `z.array(themeSlugZodEnum)` where `themeSlugZodEnum = z.enum(THEMES.map(t => t.slug) as [ThemeSlug, ...ThemeSlug[]])`. Server action (`about/actions.ts`) now also filters submitted values through a module-level `Set<string>(THEMES.map(t => t.slug))` with a type-predicate filter `(s): s is ThemeSlug` before writing to `guide_profiles.specializations`.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:817:- **Remaining gap:** Guides who completed the wizard BEFORE this fix still have `specializations = '{}'`. A SQL backfill migration is needed to canonicalise any overlap between the free-text `specialties` column and valid `ThemeSlug` values, then write results to `specializations`. Pre-fix guides remain invisible to `?spec=` filtering until backfill runs.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:847:- **Fix:** quantumbek-side N/A (this is provodnik product code). provodnik `41cbeb7` + migration `20260516000001`: (1) `themes.ts` slot 8 `photo`/Camera → `religion`/Church + the `ThemeSlug` type; propagates automatically to the request form, request schema, guide profiles, `/guides` filter+search and listings because E-10 had already routed every surface through `THEMES`. (2) `public-listings/mapper.ts` — `THEME_SLUGS` now derives from `THEMES` (it had been a hand-copied list — the same drift class); `Фотография`/`Фотопрогулки`→`photo` legacy entries dropped, `Религия`→`religion` added. (3) Migration: `guide_specializations_valid` CHECK swapped `photo`→`religion`, after stripping stale `photo` values from `guide_profiles.specializations` + `traveler_requests.interests`. Applied to prod via the Supabase Management API; constraint verified.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:854:- **Symptom:** Two production flows were silently broken. (1) Creating a traveler request on `/traveler/requests/new` failed server-side with `column traveler_requests.date_flexibility does not exist` (Postgres 42703) — every submit, every mode. (2) Guide search on `/guides` had no `search_guides` RPC to call. Both surfaced 2026-05-19 during a live browser walk of the command-center epic — not by any test (200 unit/integration tests were green throughout).\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:855:- **Root Cause:** Migration *files* existed in `supabase/migrations/` but were never applied to the live DB (`yjzpshutgmhxizosbeef`): `20260502000002_add_date_flexibility.sql` (adds the `date_flexibility` column) and `20260516000001_search_guides_rpc.sql` (the `search_guides` RPC + `guide_search_result_row` view + `guide_profiles_languages_gin` index). The `supabase_migrations` tracking table is unreliable — migrations were applied ad-hoc (SQL editor / dashboard) outside `supabase db push`, so the table both under-reports applied migrations and its version numbers do not match the repo filename prefixes. A file existing in `supabase/migrations/` is NOT evidence it ran.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:856:- **Fix:** Both migrations applied 2026-05-19 via the Supabase MCP `apply_migration`. `date_flexibility` — additive `ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS … DEFAULT 'exact'`; verified by an end-to-end browser submit (assembly mode, empty groupMax → request saved + read back). `search_guides_rpc` — function + view + GIN index; verified `search_guides('')` and `search_guides('москва, история')` execute cleanly and `/guides?q=` returns 200. A full audit of all 40 migration files vs the live schema confirmed these were the only two genuine schema gaps; data migrations (`reseed_listings`, `fix_listing_images`, `specializations_backfill`, `themes_canon_religion`) were deliberately NOT re-run.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:857:- **Files Affected:** `supabase/migrations/20260502000002_add_date_flexibility.sql`, `supabase/migrations/20260516000001_search_guides_rpc.sql` (both repo files; the gap was applying them to the DB, not the files themselves).\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:903:- **Symptom:** `/admin/guides/[id]` returns the generic «Раздел временно недоступен» error page for any guide UUID — verified on three different guide profiles (a `submitted`-status one with language/region data, a `draft`-status one with minimal data, and an `approved`-status one for a real account). The parent `/admin/guides` queue page renders correctly with all five guides; only the detail route is broken. Blocks visual verification of E-33 T2 «Лицензии» block (the licenses section lives on this detail page and is shipped in code as `d8cd673` on main).\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:904:- **Root Cause:** Not yet investigated. Likely path: one of the parallel data lookups in `getGuideReviewDetail` (`src/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:730`) — guide_profiles, documents, moderation cases, guide_licenses, or storage_assets — throws on incomplete test data, and the page's error boundary catches it and renders the generic fallback. Candidates: a missing `guide_profiles` row for the test admin/traveler accounts, a license join failing, or a storage_assets lookup with a non-existent asset_id. Server logs on the route would identify which.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:905:- **Fix:** Applied 2026-05-24 via commit `beef50b` — `getGuideReviewDetail` in `src/lib/supabase/moderation.ts` now uses `Promise.allSettled` to compose its parallel lookups, so a single failed sub-query no longer blanks the whole page. Verified via /admin/guides/[id] rendering for all 5 guide profiles after deploy.\n.claude/sot/ERRORS.md:906:- **Files Affected (likely):** `src/lib/supabase/moderation.ts` (`getGuideReviewDetail`), `src/app/(protected)/admin/guides/[id]/page.tsx`\nsrc/components/shared/destination-tile.tsx:11:  guidesCount: number;\nsrc/components/shared/destination-tile.tsx:25:  guidesCount,\nsrc/components/shared/destination-tile.tsx:46:          {guidesCount} {pluralize(guidesCount, \"гид\", \"гида\", \"гидов\")}\nsrc/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:300:    .from(\"guide_profiles\")\nsrc/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:647:        .from(\"guide_profiles\")\nsrc/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:704:    .from(\"guide_profiles\")\nsrc/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:774:    .from(\"guide_profiles\")\nsrc/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:991:      .from(\"guide_profiles\")\nsrc/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:1004:      .from(\"guide_profiles\")\nsrc/lib/supabase/moderation.ts:1045:    guides: stats.pendingGuideApplications,\nsrc/components/shared/public-guide-card.test.tsx:20:    expect(link).toHaveAttribute(\"href\", \"/guides/tamar\");\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:619:  await db.from(\"guide_profiles\").update({ specializations }).eq(\"user_id\", userId);\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:643:// src/app/(site)/guides/page.tsx — exemplar\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:681:- First introduced in `src/data/supabase/queries.ts` + `src/app/(site)/guides/page.tsx` (guide search, 2026-05-16).\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:690:When a search surface needs multi-field, multi-token matching with graceful degradation to partial results, push the search logic into a Postgres RPC function and return an `is_partial_match` boolean alongside each result row. Avoids PostgREST filter-string quoting pitfalls entirely. Introduced in `public.search_guides` (migration `20260516000001_search_guides_rpc.sql`).\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:695:create or replace function public.search_guides(q text)\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:710:revoke all on function public.search_guides(text) from public;\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:711:grant execute on function public.search_guides(text) to anon, authenticated, service_role;\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:718:const { data: searchRows, error } = await db.rpc(\"search_guides\", {\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:738:  guides.length > 0 && guides.some((g) => g.isPartialMatch);\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:753:- Post-RPC JS filters (specialization, region) are acceptable only while the guide roster is small (< ~500 rows). See HOT.md — `search_guides(\"\")` scale landmine for the push-down plan.\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:754:- First introduced: `src/data/supabase/queries.ts` + `supabase/migrations/20260516000001_search_guides_rpc.sql` (2026-05-16).\n.claude/sot/PATTERNS.md:934:- First introduced: `src/app/(protected)/admin/guides/[id]/page.tsx` (2026-05-21), admin guide review detail — licenses panel.\nsrc/lib/supabase/database.types.ts:248:          guides_count: number\nsrc/lib/supabase/database.types.ts:262:          guides_count?: number\nsrc/lib/supabase/database.types.ts:276:          guides_count?: number\nsrc/lib/supabase/database.types.ts:903:      guide_profiles: {\nsrc/lib/supabase/database.types.ts:1008:            foreignKeyName: \"guide_profiles_user_id_fkey\"\nsrc/lib/supabase/database.types.ts:2954:            foreignKeyName: \"guide_profiles_user_id_fkey\"\nsrc/lib/supabase/database.types.ts:2973:            foreignKeyName: \"guide_profiles_user_id_f