_tests__/buckets.test.ts:48:    expect(storageBucketConfig['listing-media'].allowedMimeTypes).not.toContain('application/pdf')\nsrc/lib/storage/__tests__/buckets.test.ts:52:    expect(storageBucketConfig['guide-documents'].allowedMimeTypes).toContain('application/pdf')\nsrc/lib/storage/__tests__/buckets.test.ts:53:    expect(storageBucketConfig['dispute-evidence'].allowedMimeTypes).toContain('application/pdf')\n.claude/sot/METRICS.md:46:- Alex-feedback waves A/B/C (2026-04-11): all 11 xlsx items green (A1 B1 C1 D2 E2 F2 G3 H2 I1 J1 K3). Wave A direct edits (footer dedupe, policies borders, homepage card alignment, guide dashboard polish). Wave B new guide/traveler layout role guards + destinations/guides search grids. Wave C (this session): E2 traveler request UX (date min=today + join-group notification), D2 contact-manager CTAs (no payment copy), G3 auto-create chat thread on offer submission, J1 cover-photo sync to listings.image_url. typecheck+lint clean on every commit. 4 wave-c commits ce160ff→add2a32. Prod schema verified via Supabase Management API: listings.image_url ✓, all 5 storage buckets ✓, RLS on threads/messages/notifications ✓. Push auto-replicated; Vercel deployed. Slack patch_5 + Telegram summary sent. HEAD: add2a32.\nsrc/lib/storage/upload.test.ts:53:        mime_type: \"application/pdf\",\nsrc/lib/storage/upload.test.ts:91:      \"application/pdf\",\nsrc/lib/storage/upload.test.ts:106:      mimeType: \"application/pdf\",\nsrc/lib/storage/upload.test.ts:125:        mimeType: \"application/pdf\",\nsrc/lib/storage/upload.test.ts:140:        mimeType: \"application/pdf\",\nsrc/lib/storage/buckets.ts:21:      \"application/pdf\",\r\nsrc/lib/storage/buckets.ts:36:      \"application/pdf\",\r\nsrc/lib/storage/client-upload.test.ts:20:    const file = new File([\"passport\"], \"passport.pdf\", { type: \"application/pdf\" });\nsrc/lib/storage/client-upload.test.ts:49:        file: new File([\"passport\"], \"passport.pdf\", { type: \"application/pdf\" }),\nsrc/lib/city-image.test.ts:18:    expect(brandGradient(\"listings\")).not.toBe(brandGradient(\"guides\"));\nsrc/components/cards/__tests__/guide-card.test.tsx:13:    expect(container.querySelector('a[href=\"/guides/aidar\"]')).not.toBeNull()\nsrc/components/cards/guide-card.tsx:35:    <Link href={`/guides/${guide.slug}`} className=\"group block\">\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:164:`homepage-request-form.tsx:40`, `traveler-request-detail-screen.tsx:4-13`, `active-request-card.tsx:6-14`, and `bid-form-panel.tsx:20-29` all carry `religion` in their inline `INTEREST_OPTIONS`/`INTEREST_LABELS` maps. `religion` is **not** in `INTEREST_CHIPS` (`src/data/interests.ts`) and **not** in the DB `guide_specializations_valid` CHECK constraint — it is a ghost slug.  \n.claude/sot/HOT.md:172:`public.guide_profiles` has two columns: `specialties text[]` (free-text, written by `guide-onboarding-form.tsx:172-199`) and `specializations text[]` (canonical chips, written by about-settings `guide-about-form.tsx:122-127` + `actions.ts:18-34`). The auto-sync trigger `sync_guide_profiles_onboarding_fields` pre-dates the `specializations` column and **never touches it**. A guide who completes only the onboarding wizard therefore has `specializations = '{}'` and will **never** appear under any `?spec=` filter on `/guides` (the filter queries `.overlaps(\"specializations\", ...)` — `src/data/supabase/queries.ts:634-636`).  \n.claude/sot/HOT.md:181:**Never** add a theme slug to `INTEREST_CHIPS`, any inline `INTEREST_OPTIONS`/`INTEREST_LABELS` map, or the DB `guide_specializations_valid` CHECK constraint WITHOUT first adding it to `THEMES` in `src/data/themes.ts`. The TypeScript `ThemeSlug` union lives there; a slug absent from that file is a ghost slug even if it exists elsewhere.\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:200:**Context:** Vocabulary-drift landmine #3 (specialties/specializations sync gap) flagged that guides completing the onboarding wizard ended up with `specializations = '{}'` because the form wrote only to the `specialties` free-text column. That **onboarding path gap is now closed** (2026-05-16): `guide-onboarding-form.tsx` field renamed `specialties → specializations`, `CommaField` replaced with `InterestChipGroup`, Zod schema tightened to `z.array(themeSlugZodEnum)`, and `about/actions.ts` now sanitises submitted slugs via a module-level `Set<string>` before writing. See ERR-090.\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:202:**Remaining gap — pre-fix guides invisible to `?spec=` filter:** Any guide who completed the onboarding wizard BEFORE this fix still has `specializations = '{}'` in `guide_profiles`. These guides are excluded from every `/guides?spec=<slug>` filter (which queries `.overlaps(\"specializations\", ...)`). A targeted backfill migration is required. Until it ships:\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:213:### HOT-NEW — `search_guides(\"\")` fetches all guides; post-RPC JS filters do not scale\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:215:**2026-05-19 correction (ERR-092):** the `search_guides` RPC was never applied to the live DB until 2026-05-19 — until then guide search returned **nothing** in production, not \"all guides\". The scaling concern below is real but only became live the day the migration was finally applied.\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:217:`getGuides` (empty or absent query) and `getGuidesByDestination` both call `db.rpc(\"search_guides\", { q: \"\" })`, which returns **every** approved + available `guide_profiles` row. Specialization filtering (`filterGuidesBySpecializations`) and region filtering + sort + `.slice(0, 6)` run in JS after the full payload arrives. Previously, `.overlaps(\"specializations\", ...)`, `.contains(\"regions\", ...)`, `.order(\"years_experience\", ...)`, and `.limit(6)` ran in Postgres before network transfer.\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:219:**Never** add a new guide-listing surface that calls `search_guides(\"\")` and relies on JS-side filtering when the guide roster is expected to exceed ~500 rows.\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:225:**Monitoring:** Until the push-down ships, log or Supabase-dashboard-watch the row count returned by `search_guides(\"\")` in production. A sudden jump (new batch of guide onboardings) can silently inflate page load time and memory.\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:230:**Never** assume a file in `supabase/migrations/` has been applied to the live DB, and **never** trust the `supabase_migrations` tracking table (`list_migrations`) to tell you what is applied. On this project migrations were applied ad-hoc (SQL editor / dashboard) outside `supabase db push` — the tracking table both under-reports and its version numbers do not match repo filenames. On 2026-05-19 two migrations were found never-applied with two production flows silently dead: `add_date_flexibility` (traveler request creation, Postgres 42703) and `search_guides_rpc` (guide search). 200 green tests caught neither — only a live browser walk did. See ERR-092.\n.claude/sot/HOT.md:245:**Downstream implication:** Newly self-registered guides go through the same `guide_profiles` upsert and `app_metadata.role = 'guide'` stamp as traveler signups. However, the `specializations = '{}'` gap (HOT-UPDATE — Onboarding wizard) still applies — new guides will be invisible to `?spec=` filters until they complete their profile settings.\nsrc/lib/auth/viewer-role-for-request.ts:35:        .from(\"guide_profiles\")\nsupabase/migrations/20260601000003_guide_booking_thread_select.sql:1:-- Allow guides to select conversation threads linked to their bookings\nsupabase/migrations/20260601000003_guide_booking_thread_select.sql:12:-- Allow guides to select messages in their booking threads\nsrc/lib/auth/viewer-role-for-request.test.ts:21:type TableName = \"traveler_requests\" | \"profiles\" | \"guide_profiles\";\nsrc/lib/auth/viewer-role-for-request.test.ts:52:    guide_profiles: makeQueryResult(\nsrc/components/listing-detail/GuideCard.tsx:84:              href={`/guides/${guide.slug}`}\nsrc/lib/auth/role-routing.test.ts:50:  it(\"allows guides into the guide workspace\", () => {\nsrc/lib/auth/role-r